---
const faqs = [
  {
    q: "Do I need to be tech-savvy to use AI in my business?",
    a: "No. We handle the setup, the tools, and the configuration. You just need to know your business — we'll figure out the rest.",
  },
  {
    q: "Is this just ChatGPT?",
    a: "No. ChatGPT is a tool. We build workflows and automations that are specific to how your business actually operates — connected to your existing software, your team, and your process.",
  },
  {
    q: "How long does it take to see results?",
    a: "Most businesses see time savings within the first few weeks. We focus on the highest-impact areas first so you're not waiting months for value.",
  },
  {
    q: "Do I need to replace my current software?",
    a: "No. We build around what you already use. The goal is to make your existing process faster and less manual, not to start over.",
  },
  {
    q: "How do I know where to start with AI in my business?",
    a: "That's the first thing we figure out together. We map your workflow, find where the highest impact is, and give you a clear picture before anything gets built.",
  },
  {
    q: "What kinds of businesses do you work with?",
    a: "Denver-area small and mid-sized businesses — contractors, medical and dental practices, real estate, professional services, and more. If you have a team and repeatable processes, AI can help.",
  },
  {
    q: "How much does it cost?",
    a: "It depends on what you need. We figure that out on the first call — no vague pricing, no surprises.",
  },
  {
    q: "What makes this different from hiring a freelancer?",
    a: "We stay involved. Most freelancers build something and leave. We train your team, fix what isn't working, and keep improving it as your business changes.",
  },
  {
    q: "How long does AI implementation take?",
    a: "Most projects are live within 2-4 weeks. We start with the highest-impact workflow first, get it running, then expand from there. You're not waiting months to see something working.",
  },
  {
    q: "What's included in ongoing support?",
    a: "Monthly retainer covers monitoring, fixing anything that breaks, expanding automations as your business grows, and a regular check-in to make sure everything is performing. You're not on your own after launch.",
  },
  {
    q: "Do you work with businesses outside Denver?",
    a: "We're focused on the Denver metro area. If you're elsewhere in Colorado, reach out — we take it case by case.",
  },
];
---

<section class="faq" id="faq">
  <div class="faq-inner">
    <h2>Common questions.</h2>
    <div class="faq-grid">
      {faqs.map((item) => (
        <div class="faq-item">
          <p class="question">{item.q}</p>
          <p class="answer">{item.a}</p>
        </div>
      ))}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .faq {
    padding: 5rem 0;
    background: #ffffff;
  }

  .faq-inner {
    max-width: 1100px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 0 2rem;
  }

  h2 {
    font-family: 'Plus Jakarta Sans', sans-serif;
    font-size: clamp(1.5rem, 3vw, 2rem);
    font-weight: 700;
    color: #1C1C1E;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    margin: 0 0 2.5rem;
  }

  .faq-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 1.5rem 4rem;
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .faq-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      gap: 1.5rem;
    }
  }

  .faq-item {
    border-top: 1px solid #E8E8E5;
    padding-top: 1.25rem;
  }

  .question {
    font-family: 'Plus Jakarta Sans', sans-serif;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: #1C1C1E;
    margin: 0 0 0.5rem;
    line-height: 1.4;
  }

  .answer {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    line-height: 1.65;
    color: #666;
    margin: 0;
  }
</style>
